               <head>Commutation of services; Snape, etc.; 1263</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> SNAPES and ALDEBURTH. A roll, dated <origDate when="1263">1263</origDate>, 2nd year of
                  <persName>prior <forename>John</forename> of <surname>Snapes</surname></persName>, showing that on 
                  the petition of their tenants of <placeName key="place_105489">Snape (Snapes)</placeName> and <placeName key="place_105153">Aldeburgh (Aldeburth)</placeName>
                  the services due from them have been commuted for an annual payment, with the sums
                  each tenant has to pay yearly placed in a line with their names (in number 54) under the heads
                  of the old rent, and "pro ovibus, pro averagiis, pro ferminghund et gest et de garbis uncorum". 
                  </p>
                  </msItem>
